Wife of the President, Hajia Aisha Buhari has donated relief materials worth millions of naira to survivors of the recent crisis in Kajuru local government area of Kaduna state. Items donated included bags of rice, clothing materials and other food items. Aisha describes the crisis as unfortunate and prayed that such does not occur again. Presenting the relief materials to the survivors at Maraban Kajuru and Railway Crossing, all in Kajuru local government area, Mrs. Buhari assured that, the perpetrators of the crime will be fished out and prosecuted. <img src="https://i0.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1.png?resize=505%2C371&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="505" height="371" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-191570" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1.png?w=505&amp;ssl=1 505w, https://i0.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1.png?resize=300%2C220&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px" data-recalc-dims="1"> Represented by a close associate, Hajia Binta Muazu, the First Lady told the Fulani and Adara communities affected in the crisis that, God in His wisdom has reasons for bringing them together and charged them to live in peace and harmony with one another. She said, “Her Excellency, wife of the President, Dr. Aisha Muhammadu Buhari feels your pain. She is touched by the unfortunate incident that happened here in Kajuru. She has asked me to express her condolence to you and bring to you some relief materials. “We understand what you are going through, you have lost loved ones, property and you have been displaced. We know that, what we have brought is nothing compared to what you have lost, but because Her Excellency feels your pain, she has asked us to bring these relief materials, which include food items and clothing materials. “She also asked me to tell you that, God in His wisdom has reasons for bringing us together in different tribes and religions, therefore, we must learn to live together in peace and harmony. “She also asked me to assure you that, the perpetrators of this heinous crime will be fished out by the authorities and will be made to face the most severe punishment according to the law of the land”. Also speaking at the event, wife of the Kaduna State Governor, Hajia Aisha El-Rufai expressed appreciation to the President’s wife, and admonished the people of Kajuru local government to live in peace. <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.png?resize=500%2C372&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="500" height="372" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-191571" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.png?resize=300%2C223&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1"> Receiving the items on behalf of the people of Kajuru, Chairman of the local government council, Hon. Cafra Caino expressed dismay that, the image of Kajuru was being soiled by incessant crises. He, however, told the people of the area that, the crises have denied the local government area meaningful developments and progress.